1
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:53,080
It is said The Hunter is The
Protector of the two worlds,...

2
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:56,480
...the final frontier
between human and jinns.

3
00:00:57,640 --> 00:00:59,440
Our world is made
of two realms.

4
00:00:59,560 --> 00:01:01,960
The hidden realm and
the physical realm.

5
00:01:02,080 --> 00:01:03,680
In the physical realm,
humans...

6
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:05,440
...originally created from clay,
are the successors.

7
00:01:05,560 --> 00:01:10,960
In the hidden realm, Jinns,
created from fire, rule.

8
00:01:11,319 --> 00:01:12,720
It is the nature of
jinns to be envious,...

9
00:01:12,840 --> 00:01:14,240
...to desire power in both realms,
greedy, arrogant...

10
00:01:14,360 --> 00:01:15,760
...because they believe
fire is nobler than clay.

11
00:01:15,880 --> 00:01:17,280
Conflicts between the warring
two realms often erupt.

12
00:01:17,400 --> 00:01:20,039
From the human race, a group gifted
with the power of sight emerged...

13
00:01:20,160 --> 00:01:22,039
...entrusted to protect
the physical realm...

14
00:01:22,160 --> 00:01:25,720
...against the beings burning
with desires of revenge and evil.

15
00:01:25,840 --> 00:01:28,960
In ancient times, they were
warriors from amongst the learned.

16
00:01:29,080 --> 00:01:30,680
Today, their descendants
still serve...

17
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:32,400
...in a special unit existing
with no official records.

18
00:01:32,520 --> 00:01:36,320
They are the enforcer,
the judge and the executioner.

19
00:01:36,440 --> 00:01:38,720
And this sacred trust
will be revoked if...

20
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:42,920
...they are found to have
betrayed and killed their own kind.

21
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:45,440
They are called...

22
00:01:45,560 --> 00:01:49,080
The hunters.

23
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:08,199
Hey, wait for me!

24
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:10,040
Arif, hurry up,
it's almost Maghrib.

25
00:02:10,480 --> 00:02:11,919
There's a feast after this.
The villagers...

26
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:13,520
...will complain
our class finished late.

27
00:02:13,639 --> 00:02:18,880
Okay, Ustaz. Peace be upon you.
-And peace be upon you.

28
00:02:38,600 --> 00:02:40,920
Arif!

29
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:54,520
I worship you,
the burning desert.

30
00:02:54,639 --> 00:02:56,840
I worship you,
the corrupted flesh.

31
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:02,840
I worship you,
the bloodied heart.

32
00:03:02,960 --> 00:03:05,840
I worship you,
from seven feet under.

33
00:03:06,760 --> 00:03:09,560
Save your servant from
the night that destroys.

34
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:15,720
Arif!

35
00:03:16,360 --> 00:03:18,600
You know right?

36
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:24,680
Who are you calling
when you recite that incantation?

37
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:28,840
How did you know my name?

38
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:32,360
This incantation
is to protect me.

39
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:34,560
No, Arif.

40
00:03:34,680 --> 00:03:36,240
That incantation...

41
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:41,280
...is to summon.

42
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:42,800
Summon who?

43
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:04,400
I want to dedicate
a poem to the bride.

44
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:07,440
One two, the cats
are on the run.

45
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:11,360
Sara and Amin
are now truly one.

46
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:13,960
I've been divorced once before.

47
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:17,839
But God willing.
I'll find a new wife tonight.

48
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:23,520
Hold on a minute.
Hold on!

49
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:25,480
What if it's my mom calling?

50
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:27,720
Go to hell with your mother!

51
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:29,440
Damned Hunter!

52
00:08:29,800 --> 00:08:32,600
You're so rude, you know that?
My mom isn't even dead yet.

53
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:34,120
You want me to stuff
chilies in your mouth?

54
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:05,760
You humans will never win!

55
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:08,559
Your Protector will fall!

56
00:09:08,679 --> 00:09:11,280
The dead shall rise!

57
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:33,160
I will never die.

58
00:09:33,280 --> 00:09:37,040
I am the Jinn of the Grave!
I will remain eternal!

59
00:09:38,640 --> 00:09:40,120
Remain eternal?

60
00:09:41,679 --> 00:09:43,080
Don't bet your head on it.

61
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:31,320
Hello, Chief.
-Mikael, where are you?

62
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:33,640
Sorry, I was just sending some
things back to their hometown.

63
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,600
We have a new case.

64
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:39,240
A new case?

65
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:41,679
Enough with these
insignificant little jinns.

66
00:10:42,160 --> 00:10:44,840
How long are you going to hole
yourself up in those places?

67
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:48,920
I'm doing a service to the country,
keeping the mischief down.

68
00:10:49,040 --> 00:10:52,200
You're elite, Mikael.
We need you back.

69
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:55,240
This is a major
murder case, Mikael.

70
00:10:55,679 --> 00:10:58,240
I wouldn't call you
if this wasn't serious.

71
00:11:01,040 --> 00:11:03,400
People killing people,
that's normal, Chief.

72
00:11:03,840 --> 00:11:06,120
I'm busy here.
-This isn't a common case, Mikael.

73
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:07,840
Many have died.

74
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:09,679
All in the same place.

75
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:13,400
A schoolboy was
playing hockey...

76
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:15,880
...bashed his friend's head in.

77
00:11:16,880 --> 00:11:18,320
A 20 year old girl...

78
00:11:18,799 --> 00:11:21,920
...never raised her voice
in her life went berserk.

79
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:23,679
Killed her friend while
they were partying.

80
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:31,600
Another old woman threw
her pregnant niece into a well.

81
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:36,679
All these cases happened
within three consecutive days.

82
00:11:36,799 --> 00:11:39,200
It's insane, Mikael, insane!

83
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:41,280
These are crazy times, Chief.

84
00:11:41,400 --> 00:11:44,440
Crazy weather, climate change,
extreme technology,...

85
00:11:44,559 --> 00:11:48,040
...people have
also become crazy.

86
00:11:48,160 --> 00:11:49,880
I want you to go in
and scan that place.

87
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,600
And report back
your findings.

88
00:11:52,040 --> 00:11:55,000
About your sister,
I know you like to work alone.

89
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:56,840
But I can activate a
special task force for you.

90
00:11:57,240 --> 00:11:58,640
Brother!

91
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:00,160
Khatijah Hassan
Mikael's sister

92
00:12:00,280 --> 00:12:02,000
A special task force
can't help me, Chief.

93
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:07,640
Mikael.
You go in.

94
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:10,720
You recon.
You come back.

95
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:15,799
What's the name of the place?
-Kuala Gerbang.

96
00:12:19,160 --> 00:12:20,600
Near Kuala Gerbang

97
00:13:29,920 --> 00:13:34,080
Kuala Gerbang,
Nature Heritage Site, Living Stone

98
00:13:59,200 --> 00:14:00,600
Inspector Mikael.

99
00:14:01,920 --> 00:14:03,320
Inspector Mikael.

100
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:04,840
Inspector Mikael!

101
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:07,720
I'm Sergeant Kok.

102
00:14:10,520 --> 00:14:12,800
I've heard many stories.
Hey, turn off that music!

103
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:16,800
Like I was saying,
there are many stories about you.

104
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:20,880
All the strange cases,
you solved them.

105
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:24,640
This.
Inspector Mikael's famous car.

106
00:14:24,760 --> 00:14:26,160
This car must be fast.

107
00:14:26,280 --> 00:14:30,960
And I heard Inspector doesn't allow
anyone to touch this car, right?

108
00:14:33,600 --> 00:14:36,400
Inspector, I've just been
transferred from headquarters.

109
00:14:36,520 --> 00:14:38,840
This is my hometown, eh, no.
This is my parents' hometown.

110
00:14:39,360 --> 00:14:40,760
Be careful, sir.

111
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:45,040
This victim,
name, Nam.

112
00:14:45,160 --> 00:14:47,320
Sorry, Man.
Man Sate.

113
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:50,400
Age, 23. Male.
Confirmed dead.

114
00:14:51,040 --> 00:14:53,440
Speaking of death,
my parents are dead.

115
00:14:53,840 --> 00:14:56,720
They died when I was young.
I was raised in KL instead.

116
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:58,240
Sometimes I miss them.

117
00:14:58,640 --> 00:15:00,240
I look at their faces, I...

118
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:03,400
You're talking so fast, why?
Nervous?

119
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:06,480
A little, sir.

120
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:10,960
Because your reputation
is big.

121
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:21,360
Sir.
25 corpses.

122
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:25,400
25 people hacked to death
outside during a feast.

123
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:32,040
Sir.

124
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:33,600
Headquarters needs
to send some backup.

125
00:15:34,240 --> 00:15:36,600
This is the fourth case
like this in a row, sir.

126
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:38,600
This one is
the most horrific, sir.

127
00:15:42,360 --> 00:15:43,760
What's the story with Arif?

128
00:15:44,520 --> 00:15:46,160
Just the usual stuff, sir.

129
00:15:47,080 --> 00:15:48,480
An orphan.

130
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:51,280
Quiet.
Weird.

131
00:15:52,920 --> 00:15:55,160
Always being bullied.
Didn't like to talk to anyone.

132
00:15:55,280 --> 00:15:57,240
Even when he did talk,
it was to himself.

133
00:15:58,200 --> 00:15:59,600
I've already
interrogated him.

134
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:02,280
It's confirmed,
he was quiet.

135
00:16:03,080 --> 00:16:05,400
Weird.
He is an orphan.

136
00:16:06,320 --> 00:16:09,400
I'm an orphan too.
But I'm not weird.

137
00:16:10,560 --> 00:16:13,640
Or perhaps, sir,
he just snapped?

138
00:16:13,760 --> 00:16:15,760
But 25 corpses, sir.

139
00:16:15,880 --> 00:16:17,280
That's excessive, isn't it?

140
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:19,560
Sir, this is definitely
a strange case.

141
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:36,800
What is that, sir?

142
00:16:42,360 --> 00:16:43,800
An ancient incantation.

143
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:14,960
The ancient incantation
is used to summon a demon.

144
00:17:18,440 --> 00:17:20,080
Take me to the coroner.

145
00:17:20,920 --> 00:17:22,840
It might explain...

146
00:17:22,960 --> 00:17:24,520
...the pattern the corpses
are arranged in.

147
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:26,400
A pattern?

148
00:17:53,280 --> 00:17:55,480
Calm down.

149
00:17:55,599 --> 00:17:57,320
Calm down, everyone stay calm.

150
00:17:58,280 --> 00:18:00,040
Calm down, everyone stay calm.

151
00:18:00,160 --> 00:18:01,560
The police from KL have arrived.

152
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:04,440
Tok.
We need to call a shaman.

153
00:18:04,560 --> 00:18:08,160
Matters like these, the police
definitely can't solve them.

154
00:18:08,280 --> 00:18:09,880
Am I right, everyone?

155
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:12,240
Besides, it's not
like the police...

156
00:18:12,359 --> 00:18:14,440
...are going to say
our town is cursed.

157
00:18:14,560 --> 00:18:16,359
Wong, don't talk nonsense,
alright?

158
00:18:16,480 --> 00:18:19,359
But it really is cursed, tok.

159
00:18:19,480 --> 00:18:22,960
The weather has turned so hot.
The crops have died, wilted.

160
00:18:23,080 --> 00:18:25,359
Our water has turned
black and muddy.

161
00:18:25,480 --> 00:18:30,280
Our people, our relatives, have
all been hacked to death, tok!

162
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:33,720
Mak Su.

163
00:18:33,840 --> 00:18:35,800
Be patient, all these trials
are only temporary.

164
00:18:35,920 --> 00:18:40,320
But our town is getting worse.

165
00:18:40,440 --> 00:18:43,320
We need to do something, tok!
-Penghulu!

166
00:18:43,440 --> 00:18:46,800
Our families have all been settled
here for a long time, you know?

167
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:49,320
All this time
it's been peaceful.

168
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:52,760
Strange things have started
to happen because of this project!

169
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:57,680
Wong.

170
00:18:57,800 --> 00:19:00,720
Don't recklessly talk nonsense.
There's no connection at all.

171
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:02,800
Listen here, everyone.

172
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:05,240
You all elected me
as the village head.

173
00:19:05,680 --> 00:19:08,400
We will face hardships
and good times together.

174
00:19:09,160 --> 00:19:10,960
I will make sure...

175
00:19:11,480 --> 00:19:14,680
...that all of us
and this town are safe.

176
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:16,440
Can his promise be trusted?

177
00:19:50,480 --> 00:19:52,080
Hello, doctor.

178
00:19:53,320 --> 00:19:55,640
Doctor Zaid.
Zaid Masood.

179
00:19:56,119 --> 00:19:59,280
Doctor Zaid.
I'm Inspector Salma from KL,...

180
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:01,040
...sent by headquarters...

181
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:06,119
...to assist in the investigation
of the wedding feast murder.

182
00:20:06,240 --> 00:20:08,920
Inspector Salma.

183
00:20:09,520 --> 00:20:12,000
Salma Hayek?
Sexy.

184
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:15,800
This town is so small.
Boring, quiet.

185
00:20:17,080 --> 00:20:20,119
There's no coroner here.
I'm the only doctor here.

186
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:21,920
We don't even have a proper
place to store the bodies.

187
00:20:22,040 --> 00:20:23,599
We're forced
to use this hall.

188
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:26,359
Usually, we just
get common fevers.

189
00:20:26,480 --> 00:20:29,440
The worst
is a snake bite.

190
00:20:30,359 --> 00:20:32,119
This one, he.....

191
00:20:32,240 --> 00:20:34,760
This one is worse than
a snake bite, isn't it?

192
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:36,640
You're joking, right?

193
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:41,040
Want to see the groom?

194
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:44,400
Handsome, wasn't he?

195
00:20:44,520 --> 00:20:46,960
Handsome.
But he's dead.

196
00:20:48,560 --> 00:20:49,960
I'm not trying
to imply anything.

197
00:20:50,080 --> 00:20:54,080
It's just a fact.
Handsome, fair, tall.

198
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:55,680
Long legs.

199
00:20:55,800 --> 00:20:57,320
But no matter how
long those legs were,...

200
00:20:57,440 --> 00:20:58,960
...they still weren't
fast enough to run away.

201
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:00,800
Arif.....

202
00:21:00,920 --> 00:21:02,320
One shot!

203
00:21:07,480 --> 00:21:10,359
I heard he even got
a pedicure, manicure.

204
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:13,599
That wedding package
was expensive.

205
00:21:15,280 --> 00:21:16,680
But in the end...

206
00:21:17,520 --> 00:21:19,920
...the hands that were
manicured became strange.

207
00:21:21,040 --> 00:21:22,440
Look.

208
00:21:22,840 --> 00:21:24,240
Blackish.

209
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:26,599
In the end,...

210
00:21:26,720 --> 00:21:28,280
...we're all just human.

211
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:30,359
No matter how
handsome he was...

212
00:21:30,480 --> 00:21:32,160
...no matter
how tall he was...

213
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:34,800
...even if he was the
district's star football player...

214
00:21:35,119 --> 00:21:36,520
...we all end up the same.

215
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:42,400
Ah, Sarah.

216
00:21:42,680 --> 00:21:44,640
I know why Sarah
chose him...

217
00:21:44,760 --> 00:21:47,440
...even after she read
that letter I sent her.

218
00:21:49,760 --> 00:21:51,240
Yet she still died.

219
00:21:52,599 --> 00:21:54,000
Sarah...

220
00:22:00,840 --> 00:22:02,359
It's just a fact.

221
00:22:02,480 --> 00:22:04,320
Such is life.

222
00:22:05,040 --> 00:22:06,840
Such is life.

223
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:54,720
There's never been a female
inspector here before...

224
00:22:55,240 --> 00:22:57,040
...or even male inspectors.

225
00:22:57,880 --> 00:22:59,280
As the Westerners say...

226
00:22:59,720 --> 00:23:01,400
...you are truly attractive.

227
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:25,400
Who's there?

228
00:23:32,920 --> 00:23:34,320
It can't be you?

229
00:23:49,200 --> 00:23:52,040
Sarah is mine!

230
00:23:52,160 --> 00:23:54,840
Fine, Sarah is yours.
You take her!

231
00:23:55,480 --> 00:23:56,880
Let go!

232
00:23:58,960 --> 00:24:00,400
Doctor Zaid, hey!

233
00:24:01,080 --> 00:24:02,760
The corpse came back to life!

234
00:24:05,080 --> 00:24:07,480
It came back to life just now,
after an inspector arrived.

235
00:24:07,840 --> 00:24:09,240
An inspector?

236
00:24:09,359 --> 00:24:10,840
There was a female
inspector here just now.

237
00:24:11,920 --> 00:24:15,640
Sir.
-Her name was Salma.

238
00:24:16,040 --> 00:24:17,760
Salma Hayek.
-Salma Hayek?

239
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:21,040
No, no Hayek.
Just Salma.

240
00:24:21,160 --> 00:24:22,880
Sir, where are you going?

241
00:24:29,040 --> 00:24:30,440
Sir.

242
00:24:30,560 --> 00:24:31,960
Is it true the corpse
came back to life?

243
00:24:33,040 --> 00:24:34,440
Where's the boy?

244
00:24:34,560 --> 00:24:36,119
The boy is
at the station, sir.

245
00:24:37,840 --> 00:24:41,080
Sir, people say
this place is cursed and hexed.

246
00:24:41,200 --> 00:24:42,599
That's not true, right?

247
00:24:42,960 --> 00:24:45,760
Sir!
They say...

248
00:24:45,880 --> 00:24:47,800
...people who don't believe
in this kind of thing...

249
00:24:47,920 --> 00:24:49,359
...will be the next victim,
is that right?

250
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:53,360
It's usually like that.

251
00:24:54,760 --> 00:24:56,160
Please be advised.

252
00:24:56,280 --> 00:24:58,640
The public is advised
to be cautious...

253
00:24:58,760 --> 00:25:00,480
...and not to go out late...

254
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:02,320
...until the authorities
have further details...

255
00:25:02,440 --> 00:25:04,520
...about the recent
crime cases.

256
00:25:04,800 --> 00:25:06,720
What's that?
-Our PA system.

257
00:25:06,840 --> 00:25:09,200
From the war era.
It's still under warranty.

258
00:25:10,600 --> 00:25:12,800
Sometimes the phone lines
here are down.

259
00:25:13,320 --> 00:25:15,440
In Kuala Gerbang,
there are two unique things.

260
00:25:15,560 --> 00:25:17,440
First, the living stones.

261
00:25:17,560 --> 00:25:19,840
Second, our PA system.

262
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:52,560
Sir, we really do need backup.

263
00:25:53,160 --> 00:25:56,880
This is the first time
we've had a case with 25 corpses.

264
00:25:57,400 --> 00:25:59,920
Look.
There are so many reports to file.

265
00:26:04,240 --> 00:26:05,680
This case is truly bizarre, sir.

266
00:26:12,040 --> 00:26:14,720
Ishak! Did you turn on
the air conditioning?

267
00:26:14,840 --> 00:26:17,000
It's on,
it's extremely hot today.

268
00:26:17,320 --> 00:26:18,880
Okay, continue with your report.

269
00:26:21,600 --> 00:26:26,280
My ancestors used to live here,
in the village across the way.

270
00:26:27,760 --> 00:26:30,120
But they sold that land
to others a long time ago.

271
00:26:30,440 --> 00:26:31,960
All this greenery
you see...

272
00:26:32,520 --> 00:26:34,040
...will change soon.

273
00:26:34,480 --> 00:26:36,040
There's a major development
project here...

274
00:26:36,160 --> 00:26:37,760
...and here.

275
00:26:38,840 --> 00:26:41,800
Ishak!
The lights!

276
00:26:41,920 --> 00:26:43,880
They've been like
that since last night!

277
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:46,760
A lot of strange things
have been happening here.

278
00:26:46,880 --> 00:26:49,120
But I'm a policeman.
I have to look after them.

279
00:26:49,440 --> 00:26:51,520
But now I'm confused too.

280
00:26:52,120 --> 00:26:55,080
I've never encountered
anything weird in my entire life.

281
00:26:55,680 --> 00:26:58,200
Sir.

282
00:26:58,320 --> 00:27:00,120
You want to see Arif?

283
00:27:08,760 --> 00:27:10,200
Kok.

284
00:27:12,200 --> 00:27:13,800
Rub this oil under your eyes.

285
00:27:14,200 --> 00:27:16,000
If you see anything
strange inside.....

286
00:27:16,680 --> 00:27:19,120
Be cool.
Alright?

287
00:27:19,800 --> 00:27:21,320
I'm always cool, sir.

288
00:27:23,000 --> 00:27:24,480
Strange case.

289
00:27:26,400 --> 00:27:29,640
Ishak.
Strange case.

290
00:27:39,760 --> 00:27:41,360
Arif.

291
00:27:49,600 --> 00:27:51,000
Do you know what is this?

292
00:28:03,440 --> 00:28:06,720
Do you know?
I had seen these when I was little.

293
00:28:07,440 --> 00:28:09,040
My late father warned me.

294
00:28:10,480 --> 00:28:13,360
He told me to be careful
with this thing.

295
00:28:13,480 --> 00:28:17,720
Not to play around with it.
But I was stubborn.

296
00:28:19,120 --> 00:28:20,600
It's not that
I want to bring it up.

297
00:28:20,720 --> 00:28:23,400
But what's done is done.

298
00:28:26,720 --> 00:28:28,120
One has to take
responsibility for it.

299
00:28:29,120 --> 00:28:31,360
Only a mixture
of mountain salt,...

300
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:35,640
...soil and black pepper
can stop this thing.

301
00:28:37,200 --> 00:28:41,600
He gave it to me.
He said he would protect me.

302
00:28:42,480 --> 00:28:43,880
Protect you from what, Arif?

303
00:28:46,200 --> 00:28:47,680
Protect you from whom?

304
00:28:49,280 --> 00:28:53,320
Protect me from the thing
that disturbs me.

305
00:28:54,080 --> 00:28:55,480
When I go to school.

306
00:28:56,600 --> 00:28:58,040
When I go to pray.

307
00:29:00,040 --> 00:29:02,200
When I go to bathe.

308
00:29:04,320 --> 00:29:05,720
When I try to sleep.

309
00:29:07,880 --> 00:29:10,200
That thing
always disturbs me!

310
00:29:15,200 --> 00:29:16,600
You damned Hunter!

311
00:29:41,400 --> 00:29:42,800
Kok, wake up!

312
00:30:05,560 --> 00:30:07,720
Leave this boy, demon!

313
00:30:27,400 --> 00:30:29,920
Jinn Level 13

314
00:30:30,040 --> 00:30:31,440
Sergeant Kok.

315
00:30:33,240 --> 00:30:34,880
Quickly, take him.

316
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:36,800
Damned Hunter!

317
00:30:37,280 --> 00:30:38,720
We, the Jinn 13...

318
00:30:38,840 --> 00:30:41,880
...can't wait to meet you
at the cursed ground!

319
00:30:49,280 --> 00:30:52,080
Don't shoot!
Leave it, don't shoot!

320
00:31:02,560 --> 00:31:06,560
Brother!
It hurts like hell!

321
00:31:16,160 --> 00:31:18,960
Your sister is now with us.

322
00:31:40,120 --> 00:31:43,560
The End will return!

323
00:31:50,200 --> 00:31:53,040
Sir.
What was that just now?

324
00:31:53,160 --> 00:31:56,400
Didn't all of you see it?
Why am I speaking Cantonese?

325
00:31:57,840 --> 00:31:59,240
Just now, didn't
all of you see it?

326
00:31:59,760 --> 00:32:01,520
See what, sir?
There was nothing.

327
00:32:02,080 --> 00:32:04,720
Never mind. You take Arif
to the clinic first.

328
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:07,080
Now, quickly!

329
00:32:08,760 --> 00:32:10,720
You're right, Kok.

330
00:32:11,560 --> 00:32:13,120
We need to call for backup.

331
00:32:31,200 --> 00:32:34,800
I know.
You know.

332
00:32:35,520 --> 00:32:36,960
Every one knows.

333
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:40,520
With me, I sell
all sorts of things.

334
00:32:41,160 --> 00:32:45,240
Right? But everything
I sell is special.

335
00:32:45,360 --> 00:32:46,840
However, today...

336
00:32:47,280 --> 00:32:49,880
...the most special
and premium item.

337
00:32:53,080 --> 00:32:54,480
A three day,
two night...

338
00:32:54,600 --> 00:32:56,040
...diamond honeymoon
package to Phuket.

339
00:32:56,160 --> 00:32:59,400
Okay? It's a yes?
-No, I...

340
00:32:59,520 --> 00:33:01,760
Datuk, it's only RM1,500.

341
00:33:01,880 --> 00:33:03,360
My place has the best price.

342
00:33:03,480 --> 00:33:04,880
Other places don't have
prices like this.

343
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:08,040
I'm the only one offering
such a cheap package, Datuk.

344
00:33:08,160 --> 00:33:10,240
Winston, I'm looking
for something else.

345
00:33:13,600 --> 00:33:15,720
Winston has the solution.
This one.

346
00:33:16,600 --> 00:33:18,040
A magic pillow.

347
00:33:18,160 --> 00:33:20,480
Because your face looks like you
haven't had enough sleep, right?

348
00:33:20,600 --> 00:33:23,120
This pillow can
massage your back.

349
00:33:23,240 --> 00:33:26,160
So, every night you will
only have sweet dreams.

350
00:33:26,480 --> 00:33:27,880
All night long.

351
00:33:28,200 --> 00:33:29,600
Winston.
-All night long.

352
00:33:29,720 --> 00:33:31,120
Can you be quiet for a moment?

353
00:33:31,600 --> 00:33:33,080
I actually...

354
00:33:33,600 --> 00:33:35,080
I want a protective charm.

355
00:33:35,200 --> 00:33:36,880
I think I've been
hexed right now.

356
00:33:37,200 --> 00:33:39,480
Many people are envious of me
and dissatisfied with me.

357
00:33:39,600 --> 00:33:41,720
No, no, no.
Datuk.

358
00:33:42,240 --> 00:33:43,840
A vacation package is fine.

359
00:33:43,960 --> 00:33:45,640
A massage pillow, no problem.

360
00:33:45,760 --> 00:33:47,440
But messing with
these dark things.....

361
00:33:47,560 --> 00:33:49,080
Do you think I sell that
kind of superstitious stuff?

362
00:33:49,200 --> 00:33:51,520
But my friend said...
-No, no, no.

363
00:33:51,640 --> 00:33:55,560
Your friends should be
telling you to pray.

364
00:33:55,680 --> 00:33:57,640
Remember God.
Do good deeds.

365
00:33:59,480 --> 00:34:00,960
A talisman with the
tears of a fairy.

366
00:34:01,080 --> 00:34:04,320
Can be called a protective charm.
Only RM39.99.

367
00:34:04,440 --> 00:34:05,840
This is what I want.
-Good.

368
00:34:06,280 --> 00:34:08,160
I want two.
-Excellent.

369
00:34:08,880 --> 00:34:10,320
Sure you don't want
to go to Phuket?

370
00:34:10,440 --> 00:34:11,840
No.

371
00:34:14,840 --> 00:34:16,239
I'll keep the change.

372
00:34:16,360 --> 00:34:18,239
But, next time if you need
to find me, look for me, okay?

373
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:20,560
Look for me, as long as
we won't end up in jail.

374
00:34:20,680 --> 00:34:22,080
Peace be upon you.

375
00:34:24,480 --> 00:34:26,239
How come you show up suddenly?

376
00:34:27,120 --> 00:34:28,520
You're just scaring
my customers.

377
00:34:28,640 --> 00:34:30,840
Your face looks so fierce
when you look like that.

378
00:34:31,360 --> 00:34:33,320
You should have called.
Why didn't you call me?

379
00:34:33,440 --> 00:34:35,000
You're using a cheap line
for your phone.

380
00:34:35,120 --> 00:34:36,520
Even if I call,
I can't get through.

381
00:34:37,800 --> 00:34:39,360
Your excuses.

382
00:34:41,800 --> 00:34:43,760
Do you have any new stock?

383
00:34:43,880 --> 00:34:45,640
Everything you
gave me is finished.

384
00:34:47,120 --> 00:34:50,040
Finished?
What did you use it all for?

385
00:34:50,160 --> 00:34:52,680
You know my goods are rare.
Limited.

386
00:34:52,800 --> 00:34:57,040
You treat my stuff like you're
handing out candy at an orphanage?

387
00:34:57,160 --> 00:34:59,480
Or were you the
one who ate them?

388
00:34:59,600 --> 00:35:01,000
Chasing after those little
jinns is pointless.

389
00:35:01,120 --> 00:35:03,320
What's that?
-That's nothing, move along.

390
00:35:03,920 --> 00:35:06,840
That's for a different story.
New item.

391
00:35:09,640 --> 00:35:14,560
This one I got from Medan.

392
00:35:15,320 --> 00:35:17,440
Do you know what it's made from?

393
00:35:17,760 --> 00:35:19,800
The bones of a Garuda bird.

394
00:35:21,880 --> 00:35:23,440
Wow.
-Impressive, right? Yes.

395
00:35:23,560 --> 00:35:25,440
It's very hard to find.

396
00:35:25,800 --> 00:35:28,320
I don't even know how he...

397
00:35:29,160 --> 00:35:31,480
Hey, take it easy.

398
00:35:31,600 --> 00:35:33,600
This item is truly powerful.
You know why?

399
00:35:34,120 --> 00:35:36,360
When you shoot a demon,...

400
00:35:36,480 --> 00:35:38,719
...two or three times,
they'll be in and out of hell.

401
00:35:39,480 --> 00:35:41,120
No time to even rest.

402
00:35:41,680 --> 00:35:44,520
And this one,
salt bullets.

403
00:35:44,640 --> 00:35:47,480
However, the salt is
extracted from mermaid scales.

404
00:35:48,640 --> 00:35:50,040
Know what mermaid scales are?

405
00:35:50,160 --> 00:35:53,920
If it hits a demon.....
It dissolves turns into water.

406
00:35:54,040 --> 00:35:55,840
If this salt isn't
used for exorcism,...

407
00:35:55,960 --> 00:35:58,000
...I could just put
it in my fried rice.

408
00:35:58,120 --> 00:36:02,640
Leave the jokes to me.
Don't even try. They don't land.

409
00:36:02,760 --> 00:36:05,520
And this one...

410
00:36:06,840 --> 00:36:08,560
...the tears of Mahsuri.

411
00:36:08,920 --> 00:36:10,560
But from before
she was executed.

412
00:36:10,680 --> 00:36:13,560
Just be careful, if you use this,
all truth will be revealed.

413
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:16,360
You could try shooting
a politician.

414
00:36:17,600 --> 00:36:19,440
See what happens when
you use this thing.

415
00:36:19,560 --> 00:36:22,560
Winston, I have a new case.
-You've gone back to taking cases?

416
00:36:23,800 --> 00:36:27,520
A kid killed 25 people
at a wedding feast.

417
00:36:27,640 --> 00:36:29,160
A wedding feast?

418
00:36:29,280 --> 00:36:31,640
That's why
I don't like weddings.

419
00:36:31,760 --> 00:36:33,160
It's already hot,
and on top of that,...

420
00:36:33,280 --> 00:36:34,680
...I have to wear
tight clothes. Why?

421
00:36:34,800 --> 00:36:39,600
I tried to exorcise
the jinn possessing that kid.

422
00:36:40,520 --> 00:36:41,960
Turns out.....

423
00:36:42,480 --> 00:36:44,000
Jinn 13.

424
00:36:45,560 --> 00:36:47,000
13?

425
00:36:48,640 --> 00:36:50,480
13, that's very
high ranking.

426
00:36:50,600 --> 00:36:54,000
Isn't that a Lieutenant
of the Jinn Kingdom?

427
00:37:01,040 --> 00:37:04,640
This...

428
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:07,719
What is it?

429
00:37:16,320 --> 00:37:17,760
Look at this.

430
00:37:17,880 --> 00:37:21,520
"Whoever seeks
the sacred relic...

431
00:37:21,640 --> 00:37:24,280
...shall meet the
tormented hand turning black."

432
00:37:24,400 --> 00:37:26,760
This is a prophecy.
This is big, Mikael.

433
00:37:27,160 --> 00:37:30,239
What prophecy is this?
-A prophecy of end times.

434
00:37:30,719 --> 00:37:32,120
Okay, listen here.

435
00:37:32,239 --> 00:37:34,120
"Within seven days,...

436
00:37:34,239 --> 00:37:37,840
...if seven Protectors
commit seven sins,...

437
00:37:37,960 --> 00:37:41,480
...then the Prince Jinn will
cross over and destroy the world.

438
00:37:41,600 --> 00:37:45,640
"Only the power of the
sacred relic can stop him."

439
00:37:45,760 --> 00:37:47,480
Why have I never heard
of any of this?

440
00:37:47,600 --> 00:37:49,040
Because this thing is very,
very ancient.

441
00:37:49,160 --> 00:37:51,440
Level 13,
this is big.

442
00:37:53,040 --> 00:37:54,600
The sacred relic.

443
00:37:56,840 --> 00:37:59,320
What is this thing?
-I don't know.

444
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:12,040
Actually, earlier when I was
fighting that thing,...

445
00:38:12,160 --> 00:38:13,560
...I saw Tijah.

446
00:38:13,680 --> 00:38:16,120
That thing said Tijah
is already with them.

447
00:38:16,239 --> 00:38:17,640
Don't believe what
a jinn says, Mikael.

448
00:38:17,760 --> 00:38:19,360
It's all a trick.
They're trying to mess with you.

449
00:38:19,480 --> 00:38:21,560
But I've been searching
for Tijah for two years.

450
00:38:21,680 --> 00:38:23,800
In this world, in the Jinn world,
found nothing.

451
00:38:24,080 --> 00:38:26,800
Then suddenly today I saw
Tijah in that small town.

452
00:38:26,920 --> 00:38:30,920
If Tijah is involved in this,
it's bad news, Mikael.

453
00:38:31,040 --> 00:38:32,719
The gravy has already been
spilled on the rice,...

454
00:38:32,840 --> 00:38:34,520
...you can't take it back out.
You can't U turn.

455
00:38:34,640 --> 00:38:37,080
You see that turn in the road?
You have to keep going straight.

456
00:38:37,199 --> 00:38:39,960
This is game over, Mikael.

457
00:39:17,800 --> 00:39:20,520
Raining frogs.
Oh God.

458
00:39:23,360 --> 00:39:24,760
This is a bad omen, Mikael.

459
00:39:45,199 --> 00:39:48,320
Be careful.
There's something here.

460
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:44,440
Even at a time like this,
you can fart.

461
00:40:44,560 --> 00:40:46,880
I'm scared.
When I'm scared, I fart.

462
00:40:49,840 --> 00:40:51,560
Hey.
-What?

463
00:40:52,840 --> 00:40:54,600
The stuff is in my car boot.

464
00:40:54,960 --> 00:40:56,600
I'll give you a signal.

465
00:40:57,040 --> 00:40:58,440
You're really going
to do that, Mikael?

466
00:40:58,560 --> 00:41:00,120
One minute.
-That thing is dangerous!

467
00:41:00,239 --> 00:41:02,600
I don't like this.
Mikael.

468
00:41:03,199 --> 00:41:04,600
Mikael!

469
00:41:08,360 --> 00:41:11,239
Hey.
Looking for me?

470
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:07,440
Winston!
One minute!

471
00:44:18,800 --> 00:44:20,199
What the.....

472
00:44:22,280 --> 00:44:23,680
Okay.

473
00:44:24,000 --> 00:44:26,640
Cable. Battery.

474
00:44:27,800 --> 00:44:29,199
I'll just leave the keys here.

475
00:44:58,800 --> 00:45:00,400
Mikael, I'm coming.

476
00:45:02,280 --> 00:45:03,680
Okay.

477
00:45:07,239 --> 00:45:08,840
Winston, hurry!

478
00:45:13,719 --> 00:45:15,120
Wake up!

479
00:45:18,680 --> 00:45:20,080
Mikael!

480
00:45:32,199 --> 00:45:33,680
Why is this broken?

481
00:45:44,160 --> 00:45:46,760
Mikael!
Are you okay?

482
00:45:51,400 --> 00:45:53,920
One, two, three!

483
00:45:59,160 --> 00:46:01,360
Are you okay?
-I'm okay.

484
00:46:05,880 --> 00:46:07,320
I'm back.

485
00:46:11,880 --> 00:46:14,000
Can you please not do
things like this?

486
00:46:18,600 --> 00:46:21,400
I may have a big body,
but I'm a coward, you know?

487
00:46:23,040 --> 00:46:26,199
Winston.
You're coming with me.

488
00:46:28,600 --> 00:46:31,160
We're going to Kuala Gerbang.
-Me?

489
00:46:31,280 --> 00:46:34,280
Oh, no, no, no.
I have to mind the shop.

490
00:46:34,400 --> 00:46:38,120
And besides,
when it comes to shooting,...

491
00:46:38,239 --> 00:46:41,600
That's your job.
That.

492
00:46:43,400 --> 00:46:46,520
But Winston, we have...
We have a responsibility.

493
00:46:47,840 --> 00:46:49,239
Winston.

494
00:46:52,480 --> 00:46:54,239
It's dark,
it's late.

495
00:46:54,360 --> 00:46:56,120
It's too late,
people want to sleep.

496
00:46:57,760 --> 00:46:59,160
I'm very tired.

497
00:47:01,280 --> 00:47:02,680
Winston!

498
00:47:03,719 --> 00:47:06,480
Winston!

499
00:47:27,199 --> 00:47:30,080
Brother. Hurry up,
everyone is waiting.

500
00:47:30,600 --> 00:47:32,160
Intan said
we can't have lunch...

501
00:47:32,280 --> 00:47:35,560
...until our
police hero arrives.

502
00:47:37,160 --> 00:47:38,600
Who's the hero?

503
00:47:38,719 --> 00:47:40,800
It's fine, let's just wait
until this 'hero' gets here.

504
00:47:55,719 --> 00:47:58,520
You're the one
who gave her to us.

505
00:47:58,640 --> 00:48:00,040
Brother.

506
00:48:04,120 --> 00:48:06,520
Tijah!
-Mikael!

507
00:48:10,160 --> 00:48:12,080
Inspector!

508
00:48:12,360 --> 00:48:15,199
Inspector!

509
00:48:15,760 --> 00:48:18,280
Inspector, Inspector, Inspector.
-Just a moment.

510
00:48:24,719 --> 00:48:26,120
Inspector!

511
00:48:30,160 --> 00:48:31,560
Inspector, Inspector, Inspector.

512
00:48:32,680 --> 00:48:35,520
Just a moment.
-We have an emergency case.

513
00:48:35,880 --> 00:48:37,520
They were playing Mahjong
at the kopitiam.

514
00:48:37,640 --> 00:48:39,800
Then, Uncle Wong
won from the Wall...

515
00:48:39,920 --> 00:48:41,400
...and realized
it was a false win.

516
00:48:41,520 --> 00:48:43,160
After that, he took the
Mahjong tile, and he.....

517
00:48:43,280 --> 00:48:44,680
I don't know how to explain it.

518
00:48:44,800 --> 00:48:46,280
Sir, you have to come.
You'll follow me, yes?

519
00:48:46,400 --> 00:48:47,800
Hey, Kok.
-Yes?

520
00:48:49,800 --> 00:48:51,440
Do you know what I mean
when I say 'just a moment'?

521
00:48:52,120 --> 00:48:53,760
But sir, you have to hurry.

522
00:48:54,560 --> 00:48:57,000
I know.
Can't you see I'm getting ready?

523
00:49:26,800 --> 00:49:28,199
Uncle Wong.

524
00:49:55,240 --> 00:49:57,560
Uncle Wong.
-Kok.

525
00:50:07,440 --> 00:50:08,840
Uncle Wong, stop.

526
00:50:14,440 --> 00:50:15,840
Stop it.

527
00:50:16,680 --> 00:50:19,280
Inspector.
Help me.

528
00:50:20,040 --> 00:50:23,200
He forced me.

529
00:50:24,560 --> 00:50:26,160
Stop it!

530
00:50:26,560 --> 00:50:28,080
Demon!

531
00:50:32,360 --> 00:50:36,520
You want to kill me like you
killed your sister, Hunter.

532
00:50:39,720 --> 00:50:43,000
Do you know where she is?
She's here!

533
00:51:01,880 --> 00:51:04,480
So it's you again.
Where's my sister?!

534
00:51:05,160 --> 00:51:07,720
Please don't hit me.
Please.

535
00:51:10,600 --> 00:51:12,520
Uncle Wong, stop!

536
00:51:37,600 --> 00:51:39,200
All of you will fall...

537
00:51:39,320 --> 00:51:41,560
...and you will all
become our slaves.

538
00:51:41,680 --> 00:51:45,040
Uncle Wong, don't move!

539
00:51:46,240 --> 00:51:47,640
I am the police!

540
00:51:47,760 --> 00:51:49,480
Let me see your IC
and driving licence!

541
00:51:53,240 --> 00:51:56,000
Hey!
Thirsty?

542
00:51:57,200 --> 00:51:58,960
Dew from Mount Lighting!

543
00:52:05,880 --> 00:52:08,360
Your Protector will fall!

544
00:52:08,760 --> 00:52:11,360
And you will all
become our slaves.

545
00:52:20,880 --> 00:52:23,160
Mikael.
Get up.

546
00:52:24,520 --> 00:52:26,080
Just now you
seemed almost dead.

547
00:52:27,760 --> 00:52:29,160
Thanks.

548
00:52:31,000 --> 00:52:32,600
I was just about
to get him under control.

549
00:52:34,840 --> 00:52:36,240
Oh, really?
-Yes.

550
00:52:37,040 --> 00:52:38,440
Alright.

551
00:52:38,560 --> 00:52:40,360
You said you didn't want
to join in. Why did you come?

552
00:52:41,600 --> 00:52:43,960
I was thinking.....

553
00:52:44,080 --> 00:52:47,120
You were right.
We have a responsibility.

554
00:52:47,240 --> 00:52:49,240
Besides, I don't want
to be at the market later...

555
00:52:49,360 --> 00:52:51,360
...if that jinn comes back
and I'm all alone.

556
00:52:51,480 --> 00:52:53,760
But consider yourself lucky.
If not, you kind of.....

557
00:52:54,600 --> 00:52:56,240
You should be thanking
this thing.

558
00:52:57,880 --> 00:52:59,280
Winston.

559
00:52:59,400 --> 00:53:00,800
We need to find out
who the Protector is...

560
00:53:00,920 --> 00:53:02,360
...that the jinn
was talking about.

561
00:53:02,880 --> 00:53:04,320
Oh, right.

562
00:53:08,160 --> 00:53:09,560
Hey.

563
00:53:11,800 --> 00:53:13,320
Kok.

564
00:53:15,040 --> 00:53:16,440
Winston.

565
00:53:19,160 --> 00:53:22,360
Isn't Winston a guy's name?
Right?

566
00:53:23,600 --> 00:53:25,320
Kok isn't a name.....

567
00:53:27,400 --> 00:53:29,840
The last time
I saw Saiful was...

568
00:53:30,480 --> 00:53:32,880
...after Arif
went on a rampage.

569
00:53:33,400 --> 00:53:35,560
After that,
no one has seen him.

570
00:53:36,760 --> 00:53:38,840
And, he didn't
come home last night.

571
00:53:40,080 --> 00:53:41,520
Understood. Okay.

572
00:53:41,640 --> 00:53:46,280
Later I'll ask around,
see if anyone has spotted him.

573
00:53:46,400 --> 00:53:48,320
Saiful has never
done anything like this.

574
00:53:48,920 --> 00:53:51,600
Usually, wherever he goes,
he would tell someone.

575
00:53:52,720 --> 00:53:56,000
I hope the boy is okay.
Thank you.

576
00:53:56,680 --> 00:53:58,200
Tok!

577
00:53:58,560 --> 00:54:00,280
What has happened
to our village?

578
00:54:00,400 --> 00:54:01,920
First, it was Arif.

579
00:54:02,040 --> 00:54:04,040
Then, Uncle Wong.

580
00:54:04,160 --> 00:54:06,880
Our town is cursed.

581
00:54:07,000 --> 00:54:09,120
Look at this insane eclipse.

582
00:54:09,240 --> 00:54:12,080
What's next?
Flooding?

583
00:54:12,200 --> 00:54:13,880
Tsunami? Tornadoes?

584
00:54:14,200 --> 00:54:16,080
A river of blood?

585
00:54:16,200 --> 00:54:18,280
Tok, this is indeed illogical.

586
00:54:18,400 --> 00:54:21,760
But if we look at the correlation
that Uncle Wong mentioned...

587
00:54:21,880 --> 00:54:27,600
...this is related to
the developers who came here.

588
00:54:28,200 --> 00:54:30,120
Our town is cursed, Tok.

589
00:54:30,240 --> 00:54:31,960
We should just call a shaman.

590
00:54:32,080 --> 00:54:33,800
Just cancel this project, Tok!

591
00:54:33,920 --> 00:54:35,600
It's not a solution
to the paradox,...

592
00:54:35,720 --> 00:54:37,400
...but it can be
considered, Tok.

593
00:54:37,520 --> 00:54:38,920
Be patient.

594
00:54:39,040 --> 00:54:40,440
Everyone, please calm down,
can't you?

595
00:54:43,960 --> 00:54:45,840
Inspector!

596
00:54:46,640 --> 00:54:50,000
So, what is your hypothesis,
Inspector?

597
00:55:00,720 --> 00:55:02,480
There is a prophecy
that says...

598
00:55:08,480 --> 00:55:10,280
...the Jinn Kingdom
will conquer this world.

599
00:55:10,560 --> 00:55:12,200
But the Jinn Prince
can only cross over...

600
00:55:12,320 --> 00:55:14,000
...after seven Protectors
are defeated.

601
00:55:14,400 --> 00:55:16,040
I believe...

602
00:55:16,160 --> 00:55:18,440
...the seven Protectors
are connected to this town.

603
00:55:18,560 --> 00:55:20,800
But I am not sure...

604
00:55:20,920 --> 00:55:22,320
...what is
the actual connection.

605
00:55:24,560 --> 00:55:28,160
His talk is crazier than mine.

606
00:55:28,280 --> 00:55:30,400
Mak Su, Dr. Zaid, everyone.

607
00:55:30,520 --> 00:55:32,240
Why don't everyone
just go back first?

608
00:55:32,360 --> 00:55:34,720
If there's anything
we will update.

609
00:55:34,840 --> 00:55:37,400
Ishak, please take
them back for now.

610
00:55:37,800 --> 00:55:39,960
Like that,
even I can be the police.

611
00:55:40,760 --> 00:55:43,000
Confirmed it's a
case of black magic.

612
00:55:45,040 --> 00:55:46,960
Inspector, look.

613
00:55:47,080 --> 00:55:50,560
We're just worried about
what's happening to our town.

614
00:55:51,720 --> 00:55:54,840
If you need any help,
I can assist.

615
00:55:54,960 --> 00:55:57,520
I just want this case resolved
as quickly as possible.

616
00:55:57,840 --> 00:56:00,080
Don't worry. We'll solve it
as quickly as possible.

617
00:56:00,200 --> 00:56:02,640
Thank you.
-Okay.

618
00:56:06,760 --> 00:56:08,160
Hello, Chief.

619
00:56:20,480 --> 00:56:21,880
Any news, Mikael?

620
00:56:24,240 --> 00:56:25,840
I need to find
the seven Protectors.

621
00:56:25,960 --> 00:56:27,360
I don't even know
how much time I have.

622
00:56:27,480 --> 00:56:28,960
Protectors?
What do you mean?

623
00:56:34,400 --> 00:56:36,640
Come back to headquarters first.
This thing is big.

624
00:56:36,760 --> 00:56:38,160
We need to plan our response.

625
00:56:38,280 --> 00:56:39,720
No, Chief.
I need to stay here.

626
00:56:39,840 --> 00:56:41,320
I have a feeling something
is about to happen.

627
00:56:47,160 --> 00:56:49,080
Okay.
Be careful, Mikael.

628
00:56:49,200 --> 00:56:50,800
Okay, Chief.

629
00:57:10,120 --> 00:57:11,520
Hello.

630
00:57:12,840 --> 00:57:16,280
What are you doing?
-Nothing.

631
00:57:18,120 --> 00:57:19,600
Give me that.

632
00:58:00,000 --> 00:58:01,400
Sorry, meant to do that.

633
00:58:51,920 --> 00:58:54,400
I'll kill you all!

634
00:59:07,480 --> 00:59:08,880
Tijah!

635
00:59:10,160 --> 00:59:11,960
This is not something
to be taken lightly, Tijah.

636
00:59:12,080 --> 00:59:13,480
We're talking about
the unseen realm.

637
00:59:13,600 --> 00:59:15,560
If you meddle with the unseen
realm, your life will be affected.

638
00:59:15,680 --> 00:59:17,080
Do you think I can't handle it?

639
00:59:17,200 --> 00:59:18,600
Don't be stubborn,
listen to your older brother.

640
00:59:18,720 --> 00:59:20,400
I don't want you
to get hurt, Tijah.

641
00:59:24,000 --> 00:59:27,560
I can take care of myself.
I don't need you.

642
00:59:30,880 --> 00:59:32,280
Okay, fine.

643
00:59:33,840 --> 00:59:35,320
Hey.

644
00:59:35,440 --> 00:59:38,480
You want to be stubborn,
is that it? Do whatever you want.

645
00:59:48,600 --> 00:59:50,520
Since that time you never...

646
00:59:50,640 --> 00:59:52,600
...found Khatijah again, Mikael?

647
00:59:53,040 --> 00:59:54,760
No.
-It's alright,...

648
00:59:54,880 --> 00:59:56,640
...you'll find
her eventually.

649
00:59:57,360 --> 01:00:00,400
Just, if possible, don't forget
to take care of yourself too.

650
01:00:02,000 --> 01:00:05,520
Guys, I've matched the incident
locations on this torn map.

651
01:00:05,840 --> 01:00:08,040
There are strange markings.
I don't understand them.

652
01:00:10,600 --> 01:00:14,360
These are marks
of the Protectors.

653
01:00:26,120 --> 01:00:27,520
Osman.

654
01:00:28,000 --> 01:00:30,240
The boy with the hockey
stick lived in this area.

655
01:00:30,360 --> 01:00:31,840
Marina.

656
01:00:31,960 --> 01:00:33,640
The birthday girl
who went berserk.

657
01:00:33,760 --> 01:00:35,160
Here.

658
01:00:35,480 --> 01:00:38,000
Fatimah.
The old woman at the well.

659
01:00:39,240 --> 01:00:41,400
Arif.
The orphan.

660
01:00:43,000 --> 01:00:45,040
And Uncle Wong.

661
01:00:48,120 --> 01:00:51,200
These areas are
their ancestral lands.

662
01:00:52,080 --> 01:00:54,400
Wait.
Saiful.

663
01:00:55,240 --> 01:00:57,720
Here.
His land is in this area.

664
01:00:57,840 --> 01:01:00,040
He went into the jungle,
and now he's missing.

665
01:01:00,400 --> 01:01:04,000
So if Saiful
is a Protector,...

666
01:01:04,120 --> 01:01:06,400
...that means he's the
sixth Protector, right?

667
01:01:07,040 --> 01:01:09,400
Yes, all this can be stopped
with the sacred relic.

668
01:01:09,520 --> 01:01:11,360
Only...

669
01:01:11,480 --> 01:01:13,360
...we don't know what it is.

670
01:01:14,280 --> 01:01:18,680
If you want to place a barrier in
an area that bridges two realms,...

671
01:01:18,960 --> 01:01:21,800
...it's usually a watery
place like a lake...

672
01:01:21,920 --> 01:01:25,160
A toilet.
-Gosh, so stupid.

673
01:01:27,400 --> 01:01:28,800
Or a river.

674
01:01:38,200 --> 01:01:41,000
It's time for us
to go into the jungle.

675
01:01:42,200 --> 01:01:43,760
Into the jungle?

676
01:02:46,800 --> 01:02:50,920
I worship you
the corrupted flesh.

677
01:02:51,040 --> 01:02:54,720
I worship you
the bloodied heart.

678
01:02:56,520 --> 01:03:03,080
May your servant's
wish be granted...

679
01:03:07,160 --> 01:03:10,600
...on this black night.

680
01:03:25,320 --> 01:03:28,320
Your reward awaits, Qabil.

681
01:03:28,760 --> 01:03:32,640
A reward greater
than this town.

682
01:03:34,080 --> 01:03:36,600
You will rule the world.

683
01:03:36,720 --> 01:03:39,960
Power will be given to you.

684
01:03:40,440 --> 01:03:42,920
Worship me just once.

685
01:03:43,760 --> 01:03:46,720
And when you are satisfied
with your desires,...

686
01:03:46,840 --> 01:03:49,720
...you worship back your God.

687
01:03:49,840 --> 01:03:52,040
Accept my sacrifice.

688
01:04:21,000 --> 01:04:22,400
Sir.

689
01:04:24,960 --> 01:04:26,480
This jungle is huge.

690
01:04:26,600 --> 01:04:28,480
How are we going
to find the relic?

691
01:04:28,960 --> 01:04:30,640
We'll know it when we see it.

692
01:04:31,680 --> 01:04:34,520
Move aside.
I have a way.

693
01:04:34,640 --> 01:04:36,720
See this talisman?

694
01:04:36,840 --> 01:04:39,680
If there's a sacred
treasure or anything,...

695
01:04:39,800 --> 01:04:41,960
...this talisman will find.

696
01:04:42,080 --> 01:04:45,200
Look.
It's already sniffing.

697
01:04:49,600 --> 01:04:51,000
This way.

698
01:04:54,600 --> 01:04:56,840
Reminds me of the
old Girl Guide days.

699
01:04:56,960 --> 01:04:59,320
Sticky.
-Same as me.

700
01:04:59,440 --> 01:05:01,000
I was a scout once.

701
01:05:01,400 --> 01:05:02,800
I don't have a family, right?

702
01:05:02,920 --> 01:05:04,520
So I joined the scouts.

703
01:05:04,640 --> 01:05:06,320
Could do cool things like this.

704
01:05:06,440 --> 01:05:08,560
Go into the jungle,
have a bit of adventure.

705
01:05:11,480 --> 01:05:12,880
Brother!

706
01:05:13,000 --> 01:05:14,400
I hated it.

707
01:05:15,160 --> 01:05:16,560
Brother.

708
01:05:18,520 --> 01:05:19,920
Brother!

709
01:05:25,000 --> 01:05:26,440
My mom forced me.

710
01:05:26,880 --> 01:05:29,000
She didn't want me
to end up like my dad.

711
01:05:29,600 --> 01:05:31,000
Cooped up at home.

712
01:05:31,680 --> 01:05:33,880
Smoking. Watching TV.

713
01:05:34,800 --> 01:05:36,640
You want to know why
my dad named me Winston?

714
01:05:36,760 --> 01:05:38,160
Because it was
his cigarette brand.

715
01:05:39,160 --> 01:05:43,000
Your name isn't Winston?
-It isn't.

716
01:05:43,960 --> 01:05:47,000
You think my name is
Winston binti Jamal or what?

717
01:05:47,120 --> 01:05:49,040
How would I know?
It sounds alright, though.

718
01:05:50,240 --> 01:05:52,400
Where's Mikael?

719
01:05:53,880 --> 01:05:55,520
Mikael!
-Sir!

720
01:05:57,200 --> 01:05:59,600
Hold on a second. Mikael!
-Sir!

721
01:06:00,280 --> 01:06:02,520
Mikael!

722
01:06:14,320 --> 01:06:16,560
Tijah!
-Brother.

723
01:06:21,560 --> 01:06:25,200
I think if I work hard,
follow orders,...

724
01:06:25,320 --> 01:06:29,520
...one day,
I would get a promotion.

725
01:06:30,280 --> 01:06:32,440
Become the Commissioner.
Winston.

726
01:06:32,800 --> 01:06:34,600
Are you listening
to what I'm saying?

727
01:06:35,360 --> 01:06:36,760
Winston!
-What?

728
01:06:37,600 --> 01:06:40,000
I said, I've always
wanted to be a policeman.

729
01:06:40,120 --> 01:06:41,520
But this isn't what I wanted.

730
01:06:41,640 --> 01:06:43,280
But they said...
-Yeah, yeah.

731
01:06:43,400 --> 01:06:46,360
I hear you.
You said you want a promotion.

732
01:06:46,480 --> 01:06:47,880
Yes.

733
01:06:51,120 --> 01:06:54,280
Follow orders,
and one day,...

734
01:06:54,400 --> 01:06:56,000
...I'll get a promotion.

735
01:06:56,840 --> 01:06:58,240
I'll become Commissioner.

736
01:06:59,120 --> 01:07:00,520
Tijah.

737
01:07:03,760 --> 01:07:05,320
I've been searching for you
for so long, little sister.

738
01:07:05,440 --> 01:07:07,480
How could you let me die?

739
01:07:09,320 --> 01:07:12,880
You were supposed to protect me.
But you let them take me.

740
01:07:14,280 --> 01:07:15,680
It's my fault.

741
01:07:18,040 --> 01:07:19,520
I failed.

742
01:07:22,160 --> 01:07:23,680
Please forgive me, Tijah.

743
01:07:24,400 --> 01:07:26,360
I should have protected you.

744
01:07:26,720 --> 01:07:28,560
But I let them all take you.

745
01:07:28,680 --> 01:07:30,320
I'm in pain, Brother.

746
01:07:32,160 --> 01:07:33,680
I'm suffering.

747
01:07:34,520 --> 01:07:36,440
Forgive me, Tijah.

748
01:07:38,160 --> 01:07:39,760
Forgive me.

749
01:07:40,120 --> 01:07:42,760
You left me
to be tormented.

750
01:07:44,520 --> 01:07:46,840
You are no longer
worthy of this duty.

751
01:07:51,680 --> 01:07:53,240
One day...
-You'll get a promotion.

752
01:07:53,360 --> 01:07:56,160
I will get a promotion,
that's right.

753
01:08:02,920 --> 01:08:06,400
Kok?

754
01:08:07,800 --> 01:08:10,880
We have arrived.

755
01:08:33,160 --> 01:08:34,600
Tijah!

756
01:08:35,920 --> 01:08:38,120
Tijah!
It's me, your brother!

757
01:08:38,560 --> 01:08:40,000
Go in, go in, go in.

758
01:08:47,360 --> 01:08:49,840
This place
just looks creepy.

759
01:08:52,840 --> 01:08:55,720
You're scared
of a place like this?

760
01:09:00,520 --> 01:09:01,920
Winston.

761
01:09:04,840 --> 01:09:07,360
Did you fart?
-No.

762
01:09:09,120 --> 01:09:10,520
No.

763
01:09:11,320 --> 01:09:14,680
It's normal,
this forest has many sounds.

764
01:09:19,040 --> 01:09:20,880
Many smells.

765
01:09:21,399 --> 01:09:22,800
This...

766
01:09:22,920 --> 01:09:24,320
Let's go.

767
01:09:24,439 --> 01:09:25,840
Let's find the relic,
then I want...

768
01:09:25,960 --> 01:09:27,360
...to be somewhere
with air conditioning.

769
01:09:29,880 --> 01:09:32,160
Serves me right for
eating six boiled eggs.

770
01:09:36,320 --> 01:09:38,600
This looks like
a place of worship.

771
01:09:41,560 --> 01:09:45,560
No one has ever mentioned
this place before.

772
01:09:56,200 --> 01:10:00,600
Commissioner Kok.
-Yes, that's me.

773
01:10:03,360 --> 01:10:08,280
Commissioner Kok.
-Yes, that's me.

774
01:10:25,520 --> 01:10:28,439
Tijah.
I love you, little sister.

775
01:10:32,640 --> 01:10:34,120
Kok!

776
01:10:35,600 --> 01:10:37,600
Tijah.

777
01:10:49,160 --> 01:10:52,200
Winston!
Save me, Winston!

778
01:10:54,439 --> 01:10:56,399
I'll save you, Kok!

779
01:11:07,120 --> 01:11:08,600
Shit.

780
01:11:16,280 --> 01:11:19,160
Saiful! Let me go!

781
01:12:02,320 --> 01:12:04,479
Just give up.
We've got a whole gang here.

782
01:12:07,000 --> 01:12:08,439
Winston.

783
01:12:08,560 --> 01:12:10,240
Aisyah.
-Kok.

784
01:12:21,920 --> 01:12:23,320
Saiful.

785
01:13:21,200 --> 01:13:23,080
Mikael, are you okay?
-Sir.

786
01:13:24,280 --> 01:13:25,720
Hey, do you hear me?
-Sir?

787
01:13:26,040 --> 01:13:27,439
Sir?

788
01:13:33,720 --> 01:13:35,200
Sir!

789
01:13:38,680 --> 01:13:40,120
Sir!

790
01:13:52,200 --> 01:13:53,800
Mikael!

791
01:14:02,360 --> 01:14:03,760
Mikael!

792
01:14:09,439 --> 01:14:12,000
In the age before Time,...

793
01:14:12,399 --> 01:14:16,080
...the war between humans
and jinns has begun.

794
01:14:16,439 --> 01:14:18,840
Once upon a time there
was a great war,...

795
01:14:19,439 --> 01:14:22,200
...the jinns nearly
conquered the physical world.

796
01:14:22,320 --> 01:14:26,800
The King of Jinns gained
immense and extraordinary...

797
01:14:26,920 --> 01:14:30,040
...during the
red solar eclipse.

798
01:14:30,840 --> 01:14:35,800
Humans join forces to create
a great weapon against the jinns.

799
01:14:36,439 --> 01:14:39,280
Seven righteous
persons were sought...

800
01:14:39,399 --> 01:14:42,520
...to use their power
of the Protectors...

801
01:14:42,640 --> 01:14:45,360
...to forge a sacred relic.

802
01:14:45,479 --> 01:14:50,320
The power from this weapon
from the union of seven...

803
01:14:50,439 --> 01:14:54,040
...banished the King of Jinns
from the physical world...

804
01:14:54,160 --> 01:15:00,479
...and imprisoned him in
the Hidden Realm until now.

805
01:15:06,439 --> 01:15:07,840
Hey!

806
01:15:09,120 --> 01:15:10,520
Wow!

807
01:15:11,800 --> 01:15:16,479
Did you see? I was like the
narrator from 'Today in History'.

808
01:15:27,280 --> 01:15:30,560
The sacred relic is huge.

809
01:15:48,680 --> 01:15:51,240
Winston, I saw Tijah earlier.

810
01:15:56,280 --> 01:15:58,760
Tijah?
-I fought with her, Winston.

811
01:15:59,479 --> 01:16:01,120
She's been possessed.

812
01:16:01,800 --> 01:16:06,439
So, I assume you used
your prayer beads...

813
01:16:06,560 --> 01:16:08,760
...to settle your sister and...

814
01:16:08,880 --> 01:16:11,240
...the jinn has left her body?
-No.

815
01:16:11,360 --> 01:16:13,680
Then?
-It's not like that. She...

816
01:16:15,240 --> 01:16:16,640
She has changed, Winston.

817
01:16:16,760 --> 01:16:19,080
She has become a part
of the Unseen Realm.

818
01:16:19,200 --> 01:16:21,720
Okay, guys.
I've finished with this map.

819
01:16:21,840 --> 01:16:23,320
So, it's confirmed...

820
01:16:23,439 --> 01:16:24,960
...Saiful is
the sixth Protector.

821
01:16:25,240 --> 01:16:27,880
Be patient.
-Poor guy.

822
01:16:28,000 --> 01:16:31,640
Jinn worshipper.
-That's considered his major sin.

823
01:16:35,520 --> 01:16:37,439
The crossing point.

824
01:16:44,800 --> 01:16:48,439
We, from clay, return to clay,
the earth is the anchor.

825
01:16:50,040 --> 01:16:51,600
The promise of
the seven Protectors...

826
01:16:51,720 --> 01:16:53,320
...is not only
to preserve knowledge...

827
01:16:53,439 --> 01:16:56,439
...but also a trust
to protect human lives.

828
01:16:56,560 --> 01:16:59,000
That's what imprisoned
the Jinn Prince.

829
01:17:00,200 --> 01:17:04,200
And he will cross here
after the final ritual.

830
01:17:04,800 --> 01:17:07,880
But isn't the middle.....
-The living stone.

831
01:17:10,520 --> 01:17:13,840
No wonder they've been so busy
buying up land in this area.

832
01:17:14,399 --> 01:17:17,600
Protector one, two, three...

833
01:17:18,080 --> 01:17:20,720
...four, five six, seven.

834
01:17:21,040 --> 01:17:22,520
Here is the seventh.

835
01:17:22,920 --> 01:17:25,040
That's my ancestral land.

836
01:17:26,880 --> 01:17:29,280
My family's land.
But it's been a long time.

837
01:17:29,399 --> 01:17:32,280
I don't know if they bought it
or got it from someone.

838
01:17:32,399 --> 01:17:34,720
But the land is abandoned.

839
01:17:34,840 --> 01:17:36,720
I once thought about
planting durians.

840
01:17:37,120 --> 01:17:38,800
But then I prefer
eating rambutan.

841
01:17:40,200 --> 01:17:41,600
It's sweeter.

842
01:17:47,960 --> 01:17:49,600
I'm the seventh Protector?

843
01:17:54,240 --> 01:17:57,560
Sir, I'm not afraid.
I'm perfectly okay.

844
01:17:59,200 --> 01:18:02,000
Sir.
-If you're not afraid, that's okay.

845
01:18:02,439 --> 01:18:04,200
But right now, we're
the ones who are scared.

846
01:18:06,840 --> 01:18:08,240
Is everything
sprinkled underneath?

847
01:18:08,360 --> 01:18:09,760
Yes.

848
01:18:10,920 --> 01:18:12,800
Sir!

849
01:18:12,920 --> 01:18:15,840
What if we destroy
the living stone...

850
01:18:15,960 --> 01:18:17,360
...so they can't come through?

851
01:18:17,479 --> 01:18:20,399
Do you think it's that easy to
destroy an ancient site like that?

852
01:18:20,520 --> 01:18:22,960
The problem is, the jinns
can still cross over.

853
01:18:25,439 --> 01:18:27,360
Sir!

854
01:18:27,479 --> 01:18:30,439
What if we find them
before they cross?

855
01:18:30,560 --> 01:18:32,080
We can do that, right?

856
01:18:38,479 --> 01:18:40,360
Instead of going
to look for demons...

857
01:18:43,000 --> 01:18:44,920
...let the demons
come look for us.

858
01:19:40,960 --> 01:19:42,880
Winston, you take
the shift watching Kok.

859
01:19:44,439 --> 01:19:45,840
Okay.

860
01:19:45,960 --> 01:19:48,800
I'm hungry.
-Same.

861
01:19:49,880 --> 01:19:51,320
I'm hungry too.

862
01:19:54,200 --> 01:19:55,640
Okay, fine.

863
01:20:06,439 --> 01:20:09,680
Eat.
-Thanks.

864
01:20:11,760 --> 01:20:14,920
You seem to easily trust
people you don't know.

865
01:20:15,040 --> 01:20:16,880
Not really.
Who says I trust you?

866
01:20:17,360 --> 01:20:19,080
You think I trust
you easily?

867
01:20:19,200 --> 01:20:20,960
Today you're helping us
fight the jinns.

868
01:20:21,080 --> 01:20:23,240
Tomorrow you could also
stab me in the back.

869
01:20:24,920 --> 01:20:27,680
I'm here to find
that sacred relic.

870
01:20:28,200 --> 01:20:30,520
I'm not here to save the world
or anything like that.

871
01:20:32,680 --> 01:20:34,320
Why are you looking
for the sacred relic?

872
01:20:34,439 --> 01:20:35,840
Don't you have anything
else better to do?

873
01:20:38,280 --> 01:20:40,680
Do you know how many
collectors out there...

874
01:20:40,800 --> 01:20:42,760
...are waiting for a
mystical artifact like this?

875
01:20:45,880 --> 01:20:47,560
Your motive is money?

876
01:20:48,080 --> 01:20:49,479
There's no reward
for this case.

877
01:20:50,760 --> 01:20:52,280
What's the point
of being rich...

878
01:20:52,399 --> 01:20:54,600
...if this world is destroyed
and consumed by jinns?

879
01:21:03,120 --> 01:21:06,640
Earlier I overheard you're
looking for your sister.

880
01:21:07,520 --> 01:21:09,000
Is that why you're here?

881
01:21:11,960 --> 01:21:13,360
She's missing.

882
01:21:16,280 --> 01:21:18,240
She entered
the Unseen Realm.

883
01:21:19,600 --> 01:21:21,160
I always told her...

884
01:21:23,399 --> 01:21:25,720
...not to mess with the Unseen
Realm, but she was stubborn.

885
01:21:25,840 --> 01:21:27,920
She wouldn't listen to me.
She went against me.

886
01:21:33,200 --> 01:21:34,600
No.

887
01:21:38,640 --> 01:21:40,320
All this is my fault.

888
01:21:45,240 --> 01:21:46,640
I failed.

889
01:21:49,640 --> 01:21:51,399
I was supposed to look
after my sister.

890
01:21:54,280 --> 01:21:56,520
Protect my sister.

891
01:21:58,520 --> 01:21:59,920
But I failed.

892
01:22:07,320 --> 01:22:08,720
I'm not scared.

893
01:22:09,840 --> 01:22:11,240
I'm not scared.

894
01:22:33,600 --> 01:22:35,640
You look tired.
Go and rest.

895
01:22:37,040 --> 01:22:39,680
It's alright,
let me watch him.

896
01:22:39,800 --> 01:22:42,240
I'm concerned about you.
I think you need some sleep.

897
01:22:42,920 --> 01:22:46,080
Not at all.
I'm not even sleepy.

898
01:22:46,520 --> 01:22:48,439
Just a little hungry though.

899
01:22:48,960 --> 01:22:50,479
Here.

900
01:22:50,800 --> 01:22:52,840
Thank you. But I won't be long,
just a moment.

901
01:22:52,960 --> 01:22:55,399
It's fine, go eat
until you're full.

902
01:22:55,520 --> 01:22:57,439
Okay.
-Let me watch him.

903
01:22:58,920 --> 01:23:00,399
It's alright,
don't worry.

904
01:23:00,520 --> 01:23:02,840
Winston, please bring
two curry puffs.

905
01:23:06,280 --> 01:23:08,680
Penghulu.
Are you okay?

906
01:23:11,360 --> 01:23:13,080
Why did you come here?

907
01:23:14,240 --> 01:23:17,280
Nothing. I just wanted
to make sure you're safe.

908
01:23:18,920 --> 01:23:21,560
You're our most
promising officer.

909
01:23:22,280 --> 01:23:24,000
Don't say that.

910
01:23:24,800 --> 01:23:28,360
Thank you. I've always
felt for a long time...

911
01:23:29,360 --> 01:23:31,280
...that I truly
have potential.

912
01:23:33,200 --> 01:23:35,120
Your future is bright, Kok.

913
01:23:35,240 --> 01:23:37,600
This town is
too small for you.

914
01:23:37,920 --> 01:23:41,160
You should lead
one whole country.

915
01:23:42,000 --> 01:23:45,000
Everyone should know your name.

916
01:23:45,320 --> 01:23:47,600
Commissioner Kok.

917
01:23:47,920 --> 01:23:51,040
Commissioner Kok.

918
01:23:51,760 --> 01:23:55,040
Worship me just once.

919
01:23:55,160 --> 01:23:57,080
And I will grant you...

920
01:23:57,399 --> 01:23:59,920
...all the desires
of your heart.

921
01:24:00,040 --> 01:24:03,760
And when your desires...

922
01:24:03,880 --> 01:24:05,280
...have been fulfilled...

923
01:24:05,399 --> 01:24:06,800
...you worship
your God again.

924
01:24:07,120 --> 01:24:08,960
Worship just once.

925
01:24:09,080 --> 01:24:11,280
Until my dreams come true.

926
01:24:11,399 --> 01:24:13,000
Just once.

927
01:24:13,120 --> 01:24:16,000
Until your desires
are satisfied.

928
01:24:16,120 --> 01:24:17,520
Yes.

929
01:24:18,800 --> 01:24:20,399
Worship just once.

930
01:24:22,520 --> 01:24:25,240
Until I get what I want.

931
01:24:25,760 --> 01:24:27,160
Just once.

932
01:24:27,280 --> 01:24:30,360
That's right, Kok.
But the problem is...

933
01:24:30,640 --> 01:24:35,840
...humans are never
satisfied with what they have.

934
01:24:38,560 --> 01:24:40,600
We are never satisfied.

935
01:24:42,800 --> 01:24:44,640
We are never satisfied.

936
01:24:50,160 --> 01:24:52,080
We are never satisfied.

937
01:24:55,280 --> 01:24:57,040
We are never satisfied.

938
01:25:00,000 --> 01:25:01,520
We are never satisfied.

939
01:25:07,600 --> 01:25:10,840
Enjoying the food?
Is there any left?

940
01:25:11,120 --> 01:25:12,560
I'm hungry.

941
01:25:13,920 --> 01:25:16,399
Who's watching Kok?
-Penghulu.

942
01:25:16,520 --> 01:25:18,280
He told me to take a break.
He's so kind.

943
01:25:18,399 --> 01:25:20,560
He told me to rest and eat,
so I came here.

944
01:25:25,080 --> 01:25:26,600
Please be advised.

945
01:25:26,920 --> 01:25:28,680
For your safety,...

946
01:25:29,720 --> 01:25:31,479
...all town residents
are ordered to report...

947
01:25:31,600 --> 01:25:33,000
...to the police
station immediately.

948
01:25:33,120 --> 01:25:34,520
Isn't that Kok?

949
01:25:43,760 --> 01:25:45,160
Rub this under your eyes.

950
01:25:45,280 --> 01:25:47,200
It's fine,
I have my own 'eyes'.

951
01:25:47,320 --> 01:25:48,720
So you can see it too.

952
01:25:49,320 --> 01:25:50,800
Where did you get
that ability?

953
01:25:51,160 --> 01:25:52,600
Let's just say I do.

954
01:25:52,720 --> 01:25:56,600
You will all lose!
Your Protector will fall!

955
01:25:57,040 --> 01:25:58,800
And all of you will
become our slaves!

956
01:25:58,920 --> 01:26:00,320
You already said
that the other day.

957
01:26:00,439 --> 01:26:01,840
How many times are you
going to repeat it?

958
01:26:02,280 --> 01:26:03,920
Winston, go check on Kok.

959
01:26:07,479 --> 01:26:08,880
Okay.

960
01:26:21,040 --> 01:26:23,160
I offer you burning desert.

961
01:26:23,439 --> 01:26:25,760
I offer you a black sacrifice.

962
01:26:25,880 --> 01:26:27,840
The blood of the innocent.

963
01:26:27,960 --> 01:26:31,360
I summon you to rise
as an army of the damned.

964
01:26:33,880 --> 01:26:37,520
I offer you corrupted flesh.

965
01:26:37,640 --> 01:26:41,680
I offer you the bloodied heart.

966
01:26:41,800 --> 01:26:45,040
I offer this to you
from under seven feet.

967
01:26:45,160 --> 01:26:49,840
The last sacrificial offering.

968
01:27:10,240 --> 01:27:11,680
This is the final sacrifice.

969
01:27:34,640 --> 01:27:36,040
It smells like petroleum!

970
01:27:36,160 --> 01:27:37,960
Petroleum is not
a protective charm!

971
01:27:43,800 --> 01:27:45,399
Send my regards to hell.

972
01:28:38,880 --> 01:28:40,920
Hey, Wong.
Go. Quickly.

973
01:29:47,560 --> 01:29:50,680
This town
is too small for me.

974
01:29:55,360 --> 01:29:56,760
Sergeant!

975
01:29:56,880 --> 01:29:58,399
What are you doing, sir?

976
01:29:58,520 --> 01:30:00,120
Sir!

977
01:30:01,040 --> 01:30:02,439
This is my right!

978
01:30:11,280 --> 01:30:12,680
This is the final sacrifice.

979
01:30:12,800 --> 01:30:15,680
Kok!
Don't play around, Kok!

980
01:30:39,000 --> 01:30:40,399
This is my right.

981
01:30:41,960 --> 01:30:44,840
Kok.

982
01:30:44,960 --> 01:30:46,360
Kok.

983
01:30:46,479 --> 01:30:48,520
Snap out of it, Kok,
it's Winston!

984
01:30:48,640 --> 01:30:50,640
Kok!
Wake up, Kok!

985
01:30:50,760 --> 01:30:53,240
Harden yourself!
Don't go soft!

986
01:30:53,800 --> 01:30:55,240
Use your head!

987
01:30:55,360 --> 01:30:56,880
This is the final sacrifice.

988
01:30:58,240 --> 01:31:01,840
This town
is too small for me.

989
01:31:10,840 --> 01:31:13,720
Mahsuri.
It's your time.

990
01:31:24,800 --> 01:31:27,240
I offer you corrupted flesh.

991
01:31:27,360 --> 01:31:29,360
I offer you the bloodied heart.

992
01:31:29,479 --> 01:31:32,360
I offer this to you
from under seven feet.

993
01:31:32,479 --> 01:31:35,320
The final sacrificial offering!

994
01:32:37,399 --> 01:32:38,800
Kok.

995
01:32:40,280 --> 01:32:42,800
Kok!

996
01:32:43,479 --> 01:32:44,880
Penghulu?

997
01:32:45,320 --> 01:32:47,520
Winston?
-Get up!

998
01:32:49,040 --> 01:32:50,439
Why are you here?

999
01:32:50,960 --> 01:32:54,080
Was I dreaming just now?
-I also.....

1000
01:32:54,200 --> 01:32:56,560
You didn't even notice, Kok.
Open the door!

1001
01:32:57,560 --> 01:32:59,680
Why are you all here?
A feast?

1002
01:33:00,880 --> 01:33:06,040
Seven times seven innocent
people are sacrificed.

1003
01:33:06,160 --> 01:33:07,560
Bludgeoned.
The first protector - Osman

1004
01:33:07,680 --> 01:33:09,080
Stabbed.
The second protector - Marina

1005
01:33:09,200 --> 01:33:10,600
Hacked.
Third protector - Arif

1006
01:33:10,720 --> 01:33:12,120
Pushed.
The fourth protector - Fatimah

1007
01:33:12,240 --> 01:33:13,640
Tortured.
The fifth protector - Uncle Wong

1008
01:33:13,760 --> 01:33:15,160
Destroyed.
The sixth protector - Saiful

1009
01:33:15,280 --> 01:33:18,000
The final victim
is betrayed by...

1010
01:33:18,120 --> 01:33:23,600
...the trusted
seventh Protector!

1011
01:33:23,720 --> 01:33:28,479
Soon,...

1012
01:33:28,600 --> 01:33:33,399
...freedom and the
destruction of the human world.

1013
01:33:34,320 --> 01:33:35,720
Mikael!

1014
01:33:37,000 --> 01:33:39,720
Khatijah! Return to our world,
little sister!

1015
01:33:40,520 --> 01:33:43,240
Remember who you are, Khatijah.

1016
01:33:46,840 --> 01:33:48,240
Who's the hero?

1017
01:33:48,680 --> 01:33:51,000
It's fine, let's just wait
until this 'hero' gets here.

1018
01:33:54,520 --> 01:33:55,920
Mikael.

1019
01:33:57,200 --> 01:34:00,520
You cannot deny your
own flesh and blood.

1020
01:34:01,040 --> 01:34:03,439
You who traverse both realms.

1021
01:34:03,880 --> 01:34:05,280
The Hunter.

1022
01:34:05,760 --> 01:34:09,080
The Hunter
as the Protector.

1023
01:34:09,200 --> 01:34:13,080
With you, we do not need
a seventh Protector.

1024
01:34:13,479 --> 01:34:16,680
You have the power
to stop this war,...

1025
01:34:16,800 --> 01:34:21,000
...and have peace and calm.

1026
01:34:21,560 --> 01:34:25,560
You don't have to worry
about humanity's fate.

1027
01:34:25,960 --> 01:34:31,399
Worship me just once,
and all this will end.

1028
01:34:32,080 --> 01:34:36,840
And eliminate all who
stand in our way, Mikael.

1029
01:34:39,800 --> 01:34:41,200
Tijah!

1030
01:34:41,960 --> 01:34:44,200
Didn't I warn you not
to play with the Unseen Realm?

1031
01:34:44,520 --> 01:34:46,120
It's dangerous.
Quick, Tijah!

1032
01:34:46,399 --> 01:34:48,960
We only have one minute
to get out of here, hurry!

1033
01:34:49,080 --> 01:34:50,479
No, Big Brother.

1034
01:34:50,920 --> 01:34:53,439
I'm fine.
Don't worry, okay?

1035
01:34:54,280 --> 01:34:55,680
I can.....
-Tijah!

1036
01:34:55,800 --> 01:34:58,720
Big Brother!

1037
01:35:04,439 --> 01:35:06,360
Tijah!
Don't let go!

1038
01:35:09,800 --> 01:35:11,200
Tijah!

1039
01:35:12,399 --> 01:35:13,800
Tijah!

1040
01:35:14,520 --> 01:35:16,040
Tijah!

1041
01:35:18,479 --> 01:35:20,760
It's your fault.

1042
01:35:20,880 --> 01:35:23,920
You caused your sister's death.

1043
01:35:24,880 --> 01:35:26,479
No, no, no.

1044
01:35:30,640 --> 01:35:33,240
No!
Tijah!

1045
01:35:33,560 --> 01:35:35,040
Tijah!

1046
01:35:35,439 --> 01:35:37,960
Worship me!

1047
01:35:38,080 --> 01:35:40,640
How could you let me die!

1048
01:35:40,760 --> 01:35:42,399
Worship me!

1049
01:35:42,520 --> 01:35:44,720
You let them take me!

1050
01:35:44,840 --> 01:35:48,560
Worship me!
-You let me suffer!

1051
01:35:49,399 --> 01:35:51,520
You are no longer
worthy of this duty.

1052
01:35:53,560 --> 01:35:55,640
You let me die in agony!

1053
01:35:55,760 --> 01:35:58,040
Break your oath,...

1054
01:35:58,160 --> 01:36:03,960
...kill those
who stand in our way!

1055
01:36:04,280 --> 01:36:07,160
What are you doing?
Mikael!

1056
01:36:11,080 --> 01:36:12,479
Mikael!

1057
01:36:17,240 --> 01:36:18,640
Mikael!

1058
01:36:20,360 --> 01:36:21,880
Big Brother!

1059
01:36:22,760 --> 01:36:24,360
Big Brother,
it's me, Tijah.

1060
01:36:25,520 --> 01:36:26,920
Big Brother, come back.

1061
01:36:27,280 --> 01:36:29,280
Big Brother,
it's not your fault.

1062
01:36:32,800 --> 01:36:34,320
Big Brother, let her go.

1063
01:36:36,960 --> 01:36:39,520
Big Brother, let her go.

1064
01:36:47,080 --> 01:36:49,479
If I don't let go,
we'll both die, Big Brother!

1065
01:36:51,479 --> 01:36:52,880
Tijah!

1066
01:36:53,000 --> 01:36:54,680
I've promised
to protect you, Tijah.

1067
01:36:54,800 --> 01:36:56,200
Don't let go, Tijah.

1068
01:36:58,040 --> 01:37:00,640
I have to let go, Big Brother!
-Tijah!

1069
01:37:01,560 --> 01:37:02,960
Tijah!

1070
01:37:04,360 --> 01:37:05,760
Tijah!

1071
01:37:14,080 --> 01:37:15,520
I didn't kill Tijah.

1072
01:37:16,080 --> 01:37:17,720
I didn't kill Tijah.

1073
01:37:20,680 --> 01:37:22,760
I didn't kill Tijah!

1074
01:37:36,360 --> 01:37:38,920
Foolish human.

1075
01:37:39,240 --> 01:37:42,000
Break the oath...

1076
01:37:42,120 --> 01:37:45,439
...of the damned Hunter!

1077
01:39:13,000 --> 01:39:14,439
Mikael!

1078
01:39:32,600 --> 01:39:34,880
How come the ritual
is still going on?

1079
01:39:35,000 --> 01:39:37,800
You didn't commit
a major sin right?

1080
01:39:39,520 --> 01:39:43,000
Unless, I am no
the seventh Protector.

1081
01:39:50,440 --> 01:39:53,560
I am the final sacrifice.

1082
01:39:53,680 --> 01:39:55,640
Without the
seventh Protector,...

1083
01:39:55,760 --> 01:39:58,320
...your great sin
is killing a human...

1084
01:39:58,440 --> 01:39:59,840
...completing the requirement.

1085
01:39:59,960 --> 01:40:01,360
I want you to go in
and scan that place.

1086
01:40:01,480 --> 01:40:02,880
What's the name of the place?
-Kuala Gerbang.

1087
01:40:03,000 --> 01:40:05,040
These areas,
are their ancestral lands.

1088
01:40:05,720 --> 01:40:08,040
My ancestors used to live here,
in the village across the way.

1089
01:40:08,160 --> 01:40:12,120
I don't know if they bought it
or got it from someone.

1090
01:40:22,840 --> 01:40:27,000
You have killed a human...

1091
01:40:28,120 --> 01:40:30,640
...and betrayed
your sacred trust.

1092
01:40:30,760 --> 01:40:33,960
Hunter...

1093
01:40:34,080 --> 01:40:36,360
Hunter

1094
01:40:36,480 --> 01:40:39,880
The seventh protector - Mikael

1095
01:40:51,080 --> 01:40:53,840
Tijah!

1096
01:40:54,480 --> 01:40:56,160
Tijah!

1097
01:40:58,600 --> 01:41:00,560
Stay with me, Tijah.

1098
01:41:01,720 --> 01:41:04,160
Forgive me.

1099
01:41:04,280 --> 01:41:06,040
I didn't know...

1100
01:41:06,680 --> 01:41:09,400
...how powerful
the hidden realm is.

1101
01:41:09,520 --> 01:41:11,680
No, no, no.

1102
01:41:13,440 --> 01:41:14,840
I'm sorry, Tijah.

1103
01:41:15,560 --> 01:41:19,840
I couldn't save
you that night.

1104
01:41:20,200 --> 01:41:22,760
I should have always
been with you.

1105
01:41:23,920 --> 01:41:26,720
Haven't you always
been with me?

1106
01:41:30,320 --> 01:41:31,720
Aren't you...

1107
01:41:33,800 --> 01:41:35,480
...my police hero?

1108
01:42:07,040 --> 01:42:09,920
You have caused
trouble for me...

1109
01:42:10,040 --> 01:42:11,840
...for the last time...

1110
01:42:13,240 --> 01:42:15,760
Hunter.

1111
01:42:19,200 --> 01:42:22,600
Torsim - Prince of The
Jinn Kingdom

1112
01:45:13,400 --> 01:45:14,800
Big Brother!

1113
01:47:08,520 --> 01:47:10,960
That sergeant dares
to drive my car.

1114
01:47:14,720 --> 01:47:16,160
Sir.

1115
01:47:16,280 --> 01:47:18,520
Has the Jinn King been dealt with?
-Khatijah?

1116
01:47:19,160 --> 01:47:20,560
She.....

1117
01:47:25,240 --> 01:47:26,640
She's gone.

1118
01:47:29,920 --> 01:47:32,120
Sucked back into
the Unseen Realm.

1119
01:47:39,120 --> 01:47:42,120
It's alright, sir.
You have us now, right?

1120
01:47:44,600 --> 01:47:47,600
Be patient, Mikael.
You will find her again.

1121
01:47:52,600 --> 01:47:55,320
Maybe I should get a new team.

1122
01:47:56,160 --> 01:47:57,720
Maybe...

1123
01:47:58,040 --> 01:48:00,120
...can help me find
my sister together.

1124
01:48:01,960 --> 01:48:06,160
Since when did I tell
you to sit on my car?

1125
01:48:06,280 --> 01:48:07,680
You look pretty
pleased with yourself.

1126
01:48:07,800 --> 01:48:09,320
Look at your size,
no wonder it's so smooth.

1127
01:48:09,440 --> 01:48:11,160
This, this.
-Wait.

1128
01:48:11,280 --> 01:48:14,200
who said I want to join your
team to find your sister?

1129
01:48:14,320 --> 01:48:16,840
Eh, that's right.
Aren't you a thief?

1130
01:48:17,280 --> 01:48:18,720
We should be a bit careful, no?

1131
01:48:20,640 --> 01:48:22,040
Excuse me.

1132
01:48:22,160 --> 01:48:25,440
I dare you to repeat that.
-Sir. I need to explain something.

1133
01:48:25,560 --> 01:48:28,080
My name Kok isn't that bad, in
Chinese it has a different meaning.

1134
01:48:28,200 --> 01:48:29,800
But it's still bad.

1135
01:48:29,920 --> 01:48:31,320
A woman named Winston
is bad too, right?

1136
01:48:31,440 --> 01:48:32,840
Eh, I already explained.
My dad.....

1137
01:48:32,960 --> 01:48:36,360
Don't forget, I'm a police officer,
I can arrest you.

1138
01:48:36,480 --> 01:48:38,680
Why are you all
bickering so much?

1139
01:48:38,800 --> 01:48:41,280
Just look at the dawn.
Beautiful, isn't it?

1140
01:49:58,400 --> 01:50:00,160
Call Jadian.

1141
01:50:00,840 --> 01:50:02,400
The war has started.

1142
01:50:13,120 --> 01:50:15,960
Dan Bront Palarae
as Chief

